SUMMARY:Astros, Luces, Rayos: Stars, Lights, Lighting
DESCRIPTION:ChamberFest Brown County presents a captivating performance of voice, percussion, baroque guitar, theorbo, and harpsichord​​​.\nArias and art songs by Sebastián Durón (1660-1716), arguably the most important Spanish composer of his day. Specialist ensemble Música Ficta brings to life the contrasting vitality, charm and poignancy of Spanish art music.\nThis program features recently published secular and sacred songs found in Latin American archives- which have never been recorded- as well as instrumental pieces by Durón and his contemporaries.\nMúsica Ficta:\n\nJairo Serrano, tenor\nAndrés Silva, tenor\nCarlos Serrano, recorders, pipe and tabor\nJulián Navarro, baroque guitar\nEdwin García, baroque guitar, theorbo\nElisabeth Wright, harpsichord\n\n
URL:https://browncounty.com/events/chamberfest-astros-luces-rayos/
