SUMMARY:Spring Blossom Parade
DESCRIPTION:\nSpring is officially on the way, and that means it’s time for the Brown County Lions Club Spring Blossom Parade! \nThis year is extra special as we celebrate “Art in Bloom—Celebrating 100 Years of Brown County Art and Artists.” Join us in honoring the centennial of the Brown County Art Gallery (founded in 1926!) by filling our streets with creativity, history, and color.\n WHERE: Downtown Nashville, IN\n WHEN: Saturday, May 2, 2026\n TIME: 11:00 AM\nWANT TO JOIN THE FUN?\nWhether you’re a local business, a school group, or a neighborhood squad, we want to see your most artistic floats, costumes, and displays! Think floral masterpieces, recreations of famous local landscapes, or your best “artist at work” attire.\nRegistration is now open by following this link: https://forms.gle/ezTDbLvtGMFfiFsm9\n\n\nLet’s make this 100-year celebration the biggest and most colorful parade yet!\n\n
URL:https://browncounty.com/events/spring-blossom-parade/
